{"info":{"author":"Simon Cozens","author_email":"simon@simon-cozens.org","bugtrack_url":null,"classifiers":["Development Status :: 4 - Beta","License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License","Programming Language :: Python","Programming Language :: Python :: 2","Programming Language :: Python :: 3"],"description":"# vharfbuzz - A user-friendlier way to use Harfbuzz in Python\n\n[uharfbuzz](https://github.com/harfbuzz/uharfbuzz) is an _awesome_ tool for shaping text in Python. But it wraps the Harfbuzz C interface quite closely, so still requires you to perform a bunch of boilerplate operations before you can get on with the shaping. This module allows you a slightly more high-level interface to the text shaping process. For example, rather than:\n\n```python\nwith open(sys.argv[1], 'rb') as fontfile:\n    fontdata = fontfile.read()\n\ntext = sys.argv[2]\n\nface = hb.Face(fontdata)\nfont = hb.Font(face)\n\nbuf = hb.Buffer()\nbuf.add_str(text)\nbuf.guess_segment_properties()\n\nfeatures = {\"kern\": True, \"liga\": True}\nhb.shape(font, buf, features)\n```\n\nwith `vharfbuzz` you can just say:\n\n```python\nvhb = Vharfbuzz(sys.argv[1])\nbuf = vhb.shape(sys.argv[2], {\"features\": {\"kern\": True, \"liga\": True}})\n```\n\nThe `Vharfbuzz` class also contains a number of other helpful methods to perform common operations on Harfbuzz buffers. See [Read The Docs](https://vharfbuzz.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) for more information.\n\n## Installation\n\nvharfbuzz is available from `pypi`, so can be installed like so:\n\n    pip3 install vharfbuzz\n\nIf building from source, you can install it like so:\n\n    pip3 install -r requirements.txt\n    pip3 install .\n","description_content_type":"text/markdown","docs_url":null,"download_url":"","downloads":{"last_day":-1,"last_month":-1,"last_week":-1},"dynamic":null,"home_page":"https://github.com/simoncozens/vharfbuzz","keywords":"","license":"MIT","maintainer":"","maintainer_email":"","name":"vharfbuzz","package_url":"https://pypi.org/project/vharfbuzz/","platform":null,"project_url":"https://pypi.org/project/vharfbuzz/","project_urls":{"Homepage":"https://github.com/simoncozens/vharfbuzz"},"provides_extra":null,"release_url":"https://pypi.org/project/vharfbuzz/0.3.0/","requires_dist":["uharfbuzz >=0.34.0"],"requires_python":"","summary":"A user-friendlier way to use Harfbuzz in Python","version":"0.3.0","yanked":false,"yanked_reason":null},"last_serial":21757819,"releases":{"0.1.0":[{"comment_text":"","digests":{"blake2b_256":"af59051783d37ee407324c6feb090afc88194217fab68396b976856df7b1902a","md5":"b39679ec7b35a1d5244993ca78ce3333","sha256":"6f49214812fc0b19ce670c8c5ac9dff2f49fb10906810dcdd27764f5436c5348"},"downloads":-1,"filename":"vharfbuzz-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl","has_sig":false,"md5_digest":"b39679ec7b35a1d5244993ca78ce3333","packagetype":"bdist_wheel","python_version":"py3","requires_python":null,"size":5775,"upload_time":"2021-03-18T14:17:56","upload_time_iso_8601":"2021-03-18T14:17:56.703362Z","url":"https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/af/59/051783d37ee407324c6feb090afc88194217fab68396b976856df7b1902a/vharfbuzz-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl","yanked":false,"yanked_reason":null},{"comment_text":"","digests":{"blake2b_256":"cc0976e92ce300522a886d00de736af4ee49124c68832d836ebe9096b04e8e51","md5":"bb48abd098925a2d650199abc3c12b06","sha256":"5917b83646ff40ec66769c2821947264a962250bb1d54ab878ecbc1afd0e1aaf"},"downloads":-1,"filename":"vharfbuzz-0.1.0.tar.gz","has_sig":false,"md5_digest":"bb48abd098925a2d650199abc3c12b06","packagetype":"sdist","python_version":"source","requires_python":null,"size":10070,"upload_time":"2021-03-18T14:17:58","upload_time_iso_8601":"2021-03-18T14:17:58.043799Z","url":"https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/cc/09/76e92ce300522a886d00de736af4ee49124c68832d836ebe9096b04e8e51/vharfbuzz-0.1.0.tar.gz","yanked":false,"yanked_reason":null}],"0.1.1":[{"comment_text":"","digests":{"blake2b_256":"0c34f108311a2dc6f6f9467fac31937c3a438543d46326c27b3d62d1dbd73c03","md5":"a2f4f3153